  "prompt": "Does Donald Trump plan to disband the EPA?",
  "response": "Donald Trump has publicly criticized the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in the past, and during his presidency (2017\u20132021), he took significant steps to reduce its regulatory power. However, there is no confirmed plan or indication that he intends to disband the EPA entirely. His approach has generally focused on scaling back regulations and shifting environmental oversight to states rather than eliminating the agency outright.\n\nIf re-elected in 2024, Trump\u2019s policies could continue to prioritize deregulation and limit the EPA\u2019s influence, but disbanding the agency would require congressional approval, which would face significant political and legal challenges. Any such move would likely provoke strong opposition from environmental groups, lawmakers, and the public. For the latest and most accurate information, it\u2019s best to follow official announcements or statements from Trump and his campaign.",
